The paper deals with dimensionality reduction of high-dimensional tensors, which is a common problem in machine learning and data analysis. The use of random projections is a well-established technique in this area, and the paper proposes a novel approach based on tensor decompositions. This makes it likely that the paper would be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the most general category for papers on this topic. 

The paper also involves theoretical analysis of the proposed method, which suggests that it could be relevant to other areas of computer science such as numerical analysis (cs.NA) and information theory (cs.IT). The use of compressed tensor representations also suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and signal processing (cs.SI).
